org.ObjectLayout

Interface AbstractCtorAndArgsProvider<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the element occupying each array slot.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MultiDimensionalCtorAndArgsProvider<T>, SingleDimensionalCtorAndArgsProvider<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CopyCtorAndArgsProvider, CtorAndArgsProvider, SingletonCtorAndArgsProvider

    public interface AbstractCtorAndArgsProvider<T>
    Supports a general element construction API for StructuredArray by providing specific constructor and arguments factory to used for constructing individual array elements during array creation.

    Subclasses can be created that would provide a fixed constructor (as in SingletonCtorAndArgsProvider), or to provide arguments and constructor values that would take the array index of the constructed element into account. An example of this latter pattern can be found in the implementation of a CopyCtorAndArgsProvider.
